The '''Casa de la Cacica''' is a 16th-century [[Mixtec]] building complex in [[Teposcolula]], [[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]].

Its current name, meaning "house of the [[Cacique|cacica]]" in [[Spanish language|Spanish]], may refer to Doña [[Catalina de Peralta]] who took possession of the home in 1569.<ref>Terraciano (2001): p. 160.</ref>

