'''El Palmillo''' is a [[Mesoamerica]]n [[Mesoamerican chronology|Classic Period]] [[archaeological site]] located in the [[Valley of Oaxaca]], associated with the [[pre-Columbian]] [[Zapotec civilization]] which was centered in the valley and the surrounding highlands of the present-day state of [[Oaxaca]], [[Mexico]]. Located on a hilltop in the eastern [[Tlacolula]] arm of the valley, El Palmillo is just to the south of the pre-Columbian site of [[Mitla]] and to the east of the major Zapotec regional center, [[Monte Albán]].

A major excavation at the site has been ongoing since 1999, led by Dr. Gary Feinman and Linda Nicholas of the [[Field Museum of Natural History]].

